constructor.details: The initial status is Init (default as zero)

returns._0: isAirdrop   Whether it is inside airdrop
isAllowlist Whether it is inside allowlist

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

publicSale(uint256).details: Allowed to mint several times as long as total per wallet is bellow maxPublicSale

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.baseURI_: New base URI for the collection

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

isAirdrop(address,bytes32[]).notice: Check if the address is inside airdrop list

isAllowlist(address,bytes32[]).notice: Check if the address is inside allow list

setBaseURI(string).notice: Set the base URI for the NFTs

withdrawERC20(address,uint256).notice: Withdraw specificed ERC20 and amount to owner
